# 28_s219_scripter_integration_smoke.curvzs
#
# s219 m1 acceptance smoke. Confirms the scripting surface is up and
# the previously-CURVZ_DIAGNOSTIC-gated registrations all happened.
# Run this with the Scripter visible (you already have to in order to
# hit Run, so by definition scripter_enabled is true).

# 1. The headerbar Scripter button is registered (substrate-routed).
#    If this fails: the monkey button didn't construct, or didn't
#    pack itself into the headerbar with its abbrev intact.
assert mw_scripter visible == true

# 2. Layers collection Scriptable is alive. Pre-s219 this lived behind
#    the diagnostic gate. The `count` query is collection-tier and
#    safe to call on any project (returns 0 on empty).
assert layers count >= 0

# 3. Guides collection Scriptable is alive (s218 m1 / s219 m1).
assert guides count >= 0

# 4. Styles panel Scriptable is alive (s202 m1 / s219 m1).
#    section_open is a query the panel-Scriptable answers from its
#    section_open_flag handle (set by MainWindow at setup_layout).
#    The value itself doesn't matter; what matters is that the verb
#    resolves without "unknown verb" errors.
assert pnl_styles section_open == false || pnl_styles section_open == true

# 5. Scripter's own controls. If the Scripter window isn't built and
#    registered, none of these exist.
assert scr_run visible == true
assert scr_step visible == true
assert scr_delay visible == true

# 6. Toolbar widgets — these don't depend on s219 m1 but confirm the
#    substrate layer is otherwise healthy. If everything above passes
#    but these fail, the regression is somewhere else and isn't s219.
assert tb_sel visible == true
assert tb_nod visible == true

#[sub] s219 m1 smoke complete — every gate dropped, every Scriptable alive
